Package org.opensextant.output

Xponents Output Formatting using GISCore

The foundation of the output formatting is the AbstractFormatter.  All implementations of GIS formats - Shapefile, FileGeodatabase, KML, etc. -- employ GISCore (opensextant GISCore 2.x).
The OpenSextantSchema class defines the standard elements that are derived from geocoding.

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ResultsFormatter
    Interface for classes that generate output from corpora that have been processed by OpenSextant.
  • Class Summary

    Abstract class encapsulating basic results formatter functionality.

    FormatterFactory

    GeoCSVFormatter

    GISDataFormatter
    This is the base class for classes that convert document annotations to GISCore features.
    GISDataModel  
    KMLFormatter
    A formatter for KML output that uses GISCore API.
    OpenSextantSchema
    GISCore-based output schema.
    ShapefileFormatter
    A results formatter for shapefile output.
    WKTFormatter
    A formatter for WKT outut.
